==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quo warranto
<hw>Quo` war*ran"to</hw> <pr>(kw⟦omac⟧`
w⟦ocr⟧r*r⟦acr⟧n"t⟦osl⟧)</pr>. <ety>[So called from the Law L. words
<ets>quo warranto</ets> (by what authority), in the original Latin form
of the writ. See <er>Which</er>, and <er>Warrant</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A writ brought before a proper tribunal, to
inquire by what warrant a person or a corporation acts, or exercises
certain powers.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ An information in the nature of a <xex>quo
warranto</xex> is now common as a substitute for the writ.
<au>Wharton.</au> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quran</ent>⟦br⟧
